## 🎯 Checklist

When generating or reviewing code:

- [ ] Feature-led structure (`apps/<service>/src/<feature>/`)
- [ ] Patterns/payloads added to `libs/contracts/` before any service code
- [ ] Gateway controller: `ClientProxy.send()` only — zero business logic
- [ ] Auth-service controller: `@MessagePattern` only — delegates to service
- [ ] `AUTH_SERVICE` injected via `@Inject(AUTH_SERVICE)` — not imported from feature modules
- [ ] New microservice clients go in `MicroservicesClientModule`, not feature modules
- [ ] `@app/prisma` used only in `auth-service/src/app.module.ts`
- [ ] All 7 naming principles followed
- [ ] Explicit return types — no implicit `any`
- [ ] Functional programming enforced (immutability, pure functions)
- [ ] DTOs validated at gateway boundary only
- [ ] Controller → Service → Repository layering respected
- [ ] Gateway tests mock `ClientProxy` (not services)
- [ ] Auth-service tests mock repositories (not Prisma directly)
- [ ] AAA test structure used
- [ ] Relevant skill files consulted
